Members of the eThekwini Inner South Cluster Task Team have been commended for arresting an 18-year-old suspect within hours after a video of him posing with a firearm went viral. Police spokesperson, Brigadier Jay Naicker, said, “The suspect was arrested at Wentworth and was found in illegal possession of a 9mm pistol with ammunition. Investigations revealed that the firearm was stolen in Phoenix in March 2019. He appeared at the Wentworth Magistrates Court.” The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula praised the team for the speedy arrest of the suspect and the recovery of the firearm.